he book of the generation of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Abraham brings forth Isaac; and Isaac brings forth Jacob; and Jacob brings forth Judas and his brethren;
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And Judas brings forth Phares and Zara of Thamar; and Phares brings forth Esrom; and Esrom brings forth Aram;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And Aram brings forth Aminadab; and Aminadab brings forth Naasson; and Naasson brings forth Salmon;
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And Salmon brings forth Booz of Rachab; and Booz brings forth Obed of Ruth; and Obed brings forth Jesse;
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]And Jesse brings forth David the king; and David the king brings forth Solomon of her that had been the wife of Urias;
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]And Solomon brings forth Roboam; and Roboam brings forth Abia; and Abia brings forth Asa;
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And Asa brings forth Josaphat; and Josaphat brings forth Joram; and Joram brings forth Ozias;
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And Ozias brings forth Joatham; and Joatham brings forth Achaz; and Achaz brings forth Ezekias;
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And Ezekias brings forth Manasses; and Manasses brings forth Amon; and Amon brings forth Josias;
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And Josias brings forth Jechonias and his brethren, about the time they were carried away to Babylon:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And after they were brought to Babylon, Jechonias brings forth Salathiel; and Salathiel brings forth Zorobabel;
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And Zorobabel brings forth Abiud; and Abiud brings forth Eliakim; and Eliakim brings forth Azor;
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And Azor brings forth Sadoc; and Sadoc brings forth Achim; and Achim brings forth Eliud;
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And Eliud brings forth Eleazar; and Eleazar brings forth Matthan; and Matthan brings forth Jacob;
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And Jacob brings forth Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are fourteen generations; and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are fourteen generations.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Now the birth of Jesus Christ was likewise: When as his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph, before they came together, she was found with child of the Holy Spirit.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to make her a public example, was minded to put her away privately.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]But while he thought on these things, behold, the angel of the LORD appeared unto him in a dream, saying, Joseph, you son of David, fear not to take unto you Mary your wife: for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And she shall bring forth a son, and you shall call his name JESUS: for he shall save his people from their sins.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Now all this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying,
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with us.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Then Joseph being raised from sleep did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took unto him his wife:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And had sexual contact with her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son: and he called his name JESUS.
