\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]And says unto him, If you be the Son of God, cast yourself down: for it is written, He shall give his angels charge concerning you: and in their hands they shall bear you up, lest at any time you dash your foot against a stone.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Jesus said unto him, It is written again, You shall not tempt the Lord your God.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Again, the devil takes him up into an exceeding high mountain, and shows him all the kingdoms of the world, and the glory of them;
