\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But he that received seed into the good ground is he that hears the word,  and understands it; which also bears fruit, and brings forth, some an hundredfold, some sixty, some thirty.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Another parable put he forth unto them, saying, The kingdom of heaven is likened unto a man which sowed good seed in his field:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]But while men slept, his enemy came and sowed tares among the wheat, and went his way.
