\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]But woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you shut up the kingdom of heaven against men: for all of you neither go in yourselves, neither suffer all of you them that are entering to go in.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you devour widows' houses, and for a pretence make long prayer: therefore all of you shall receive the greater damnation.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you compass sea and land to make one proselyte, and when he is made, all of you make him twofold more the child of hell than yourselves.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, all of you blind guides, which say, Whosoever shall swear by the temple, it is nothing; but whosoever shall swear by the gold of the temple, he is a debtor!
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]All of you fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gold, or the temple that santifies the gold?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And, Whosoever shall swear by the altar, it is nothing; but whosoever swears by the gift that is upon it, he is guilty.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]All of you fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gift, or the altar that santifies the gift?
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Whoso therefore shall swear by the altar, swears by it, and by all things thereon.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And whoso shall swear by the temple, swears by it, and by him that dwells therein.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And he that shall swear by heaven, swears by the throne of God, and by him that sits thereon.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you pay tithe of mint and anise and cummin, and have omitted the weightier matters of the law, judgment, mercy, and faith: these ought all of you to have done, and not to leave the other undone.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]All of you blind guides, which strain out a gnat, and swallow a camel.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you make clean the outside of the cup and of the platter, but within they are full of extortion and excess.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]You blind Pharisee, cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter, that the outside of them may be clean also.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for all of you are like unto whitewashed sepulchers, which indeed appear beautiful outward, but are within full of dead men's bones, and of all uncleanness.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Even so all of you also outwardly appear righteous unto men, but within all of you are full of hypocrisy and iniquity.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! because all of you build the tombs of the prophets, and garnish the sepulchers of the righteous,
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And say, If we had been in the days of our fathers, we would not have been partakers with them in the blood of the prophets.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Wherefore all of you be witnesses unto yourselves, that all of you are the children of them which killed the prophets.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Fill all of you up then the measure of your fathers.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]All of you serpents, all of you generation of vipers, how can all of you escape the damnation of hell?
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Wherefore, behold, I send unto you prophets, and wise men, and scribes: and some of them all of you shall kill and crucify; and some of them shall all of you scourge in your synagogues, and persecute them from city to city:
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]That upon you may come all the righteous blood shed upon the earth, from the blood of righteous Abel unto the blood of Zacharias son of Barachias, whom all of you slew between the temple and the altar.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Verily I say unto you, All these things shall come upon this generation.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, you that kill the prophets, and stone them which are sent unto you, how often would I have gathered your children together, even as a hen gathers her chickens under her wings, and all of you would not!
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]Behold, your house is left unto you desolate.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]For I say unto you, All of you shall not see me henceforth, till all of you shall say, Blessed is he that comes in the name of the Lord.
