nd again he entered into Capernaum after some days; and it was noised that he was in the house.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And immediately many were gathered together, insomuch that there was no room to receive them, no, not so much as about the door: and he preached the word  unto them.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And when they could not come nigh unto him for the press, they uncovered the roof where he was: and when they had broken it up, they let down the bed wherein the sick of the palsy lay.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick of the palsy, Son, your sins be forgiven you.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]But there was certain of the scribes sitting there, and reasoning in their hearts,
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Why does this man thus speak blasphemies? who can forgive sins but God only?
