\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And unclean spirits,  when they saw him, fell down before him, and cried, saying, You are the Son of God.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And he strictly charged them that they should not make him known.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And he goes up into a mountain, and calls unto him whom he would: and they came unto him.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And Simon he surnamed Peter;
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James; and he surnamed them Boanerges, which is, The sons of thunder:
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Canaanite,
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him: and they went into an house.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And the multitude comes together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And when his friends heard of it, they went out to lay hold on him: for they said, He is beside himself.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said, He has Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils casts he out devils.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And he called them unto him, and said unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And if a kingdom be divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And if a house be divided against itself, that house cannot stand.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand, but has an end.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]No man can enter into a strong man's house, and spoil his goods, except he will first bind the strong man; and then he will spoil his house.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Verily I say unto you, All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies wherewith whatsoever they shall blaspheme:
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Spirit  has never forgiveness, but is in danger of eternal damnation.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Because they said, He has an unclean spirit.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]There came then his brethren and his mother, and, standing without, sent unto him, calling him.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And the multitude sat about him, and they said unto him, Behold, your mother and your brethren without seek for you.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother, or my brethren?
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And he looked round about on them which sat about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren!
