\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And he sighed deeply in his spirit,  and says, Why does this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, There shall no sign be given unto this generation.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And he left them, and entering into the ship again departed to the other side.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Now the disciples had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And he charged them, saying, Take heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and of the leaven of Herod.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And they reasoned among themselves, saying, It is because we have no bread.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And when Jesus knew it, he says unto them, Why reason all of you, because all of you have no bread? perceive all of you not yet, neither understand? have all of you your heart yet hardened?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Having eyes, see all of you not? and having ears, hear all of you not? and do all of you not remember?
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took all of you up? They say unto him, Twelve.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And when the seven among four thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took all of you up? And they said, Seven.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, How is it that all of you do not understand?
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And he comes to Bethsaida; and they bring a blind man unto him, and besought him to touch him.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And he took the blind man by the hand, and led him out of the town; and when he had spit on his eyes, and put his hands upon him, he asked him if he saw ought.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]After that he put his hands again upon his eyes, and made him look up: and he was restored, and saw every man clearly.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell it to any in the town.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And they answered, John the Baptist; but some say, Elijah; and others, One of the prophets.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And he says unto them, But whom say all of you that I am? And Peter answers and says unto him, You are the Christ.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And he began to teach them, that the Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders, and of the chief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And he spoke that saying  openly. And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples, he rebuked Peter, saying, Get you behind me, Satan: for you savour not the things that be of God, but the things that be of men.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And when he had called the people unto him with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel's, the same shall save it.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul?
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me and of my words  in this adulterous and sinful generation; of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he comes in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
