\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Jesus said unto him, If you can believe, all things are possible to him that believes.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And immediately the father of the child cried out, and said with tears, Lord, I believe; help you mine unbelief.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit,  saying unto him, You dumb and deaf spirit,  I charge you, come out of him, and enter no more into him.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And the spirit cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him: and he was as one dead; insomuch that many said, He is dead.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out?
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, This kind can come forth by nothing, but by prayer and fasting.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And they departed thence, and passed through Galilee; and he would not that any man should know it.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]For he taught his disciples, and said unto them, The Son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him; and after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]But they understood not that saying,  and were afraid to ask him.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them, What was it that all of you disputed among yourselves by the way?
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]But they held their peace: for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who should be the greatest.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And he sat down, and called the twelve, and says unto them, If any man desire to be first, the same shall be last of all, and servant of all.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And he took a child, and set him in the midst of them: and when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them,
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receives me: and whosoever shall receive me, receives not me, but him that sent me.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in your name, and he follows not us: and we forbad him, because he follows not us.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]But Jesus said, Forbid him not: for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name, that can lightly speak evil of me.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]For he that is not against us is on our part.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because all of you belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And whosoever shall offend one of these little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And if your hand offend you, cut it off: it is better for you to enter into life physically disabled, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]Where their worm dies not, and the fire is not quenched.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And if your foot offend you, cut it off: it is better for you to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]Where their worm dies not, and the fire is not quenched.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And if yours eye offend you, pluck it out: it is better for you to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Where their worm dies not, and the fire is not quenched.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]Salt is good: but if the salt have lost his saltiness, wherewith will all of you season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another.
