\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received it not.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And the scripture was fulfilled, which says, And he was numbered with the transgressors.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, you that destroys the temple, and build it in three days,
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Save yourself, and come down from the cross.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which is, being interpreted, My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And some of them that stood by, when they heard it, said, Behold, he calls Elijah.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And one ran and filled a sponge full of vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let alone; let us see whether Elijah will come to take him down.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the spirit.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And the veil of the temple was rent in two from the top to the bottom.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And when the centurion, which stood opposite to him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the spirit, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]There were also women looking on far off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX](Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counsellor, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a tomb which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the tomb.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]And Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses beheld where he was laid.
