\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And, behold, there was a man in Jerusalem, whose name was Simeon; and the same man was just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel: and the Holy Spirit  was upon him.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And it was revealed unto him by the Holy Spirit,  that he should not see death, before he had seen the Lord's Christ.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And he came by the Spirit  into the temple: and when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him after the custom of the law,
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Then took he him up in his arms, and blessed God, and said,
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Lord, now let you your servant depart in peace, according to your word:
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]For mine eyes have seen your salvation,
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]Which you have prepared before the face of all people;
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]A light to lighten the Gentiles, and the glory of your people Israel.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And Joseph and his mother marvelled at those things which were spoken of him.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold, this child is set for the fall and rising again of many in Israel; and for a sign which shall be spoken against;
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX](Yea, a sword shall pierce through your own soul also,) that the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Aser: she was of a great age, and had lived with an husband seven years from her virginity;
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And she was a widow of about fourscore and four years, which departed not from the temple, but served God with fastings and prayers night and day.
