\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]Till I make yours enemies your footstool.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]David therefore calls him Lord, how is he then his son?
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then in the audience of all the people he said unto his disciples,
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]Beware of the scribes, which desire to walk in long robes, and love greetings in the markets, and the highest seats in the synagogues, and the chief rooms at feasts;
