\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Settle it therefore in your hearts, not to meditate before what all of you shall answer:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For I will give you a mouth and wisdom, which all your adversaries shall not be able to gainsay nor resist.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And all of you shall be betrayed both by parents, and brethren, and kinsfolks, and friends; and some of you shall they cause to be put to death.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And all of you shall be hated of all men for my name's sake.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]But there shall not an hair of your head perish.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]In your patience possess all of you your souls.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And when all of you shall see Jerusalem compassed with armies, then know that the desolation thereof is nigh.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Then let them which are in Judaea flee to the mountains; and let them which are in the midst of it depart out; and let not them that are in the countries enter therein.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]For these be the days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck, in those days! for there shall be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And they shall fall by the edge of the sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations: and Jerusalem shall be trodden down of the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And there shall be signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars; and upon the earth distress of nations, with perplexity; the sea and the waves roaring;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Men's hearts failing them for fear, and for looking after those things which are coming on the earth: for the powers of heaven shall be shaken.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And then shall they see the Son of man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up, and lift up your heads; for your redemption draws nigh.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And he spoke to them a parable; Behold the fig tree, and all the trees;
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]When they now shoot forth, all of you see and know of your own selves that summer is now nigh at hand.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]So likewise all of you, when all of you see these things come to pass, know all of you that the kingdom of God is nigh at hand.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Verily I say unto you, This generation shall not pass away, till all be fulfilled.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words  shall not pass away.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]And take heed to yourselves, lest at any time your hearts be overcharged with worldly excess, and drunkenness, and cares of this life, and so that day come upon you unexpectedly.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]For as a snare shall it come on all them that dwell on the face of the whole earth.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]Watch all of you therefore, and pray always, that all of you may be accounted worthy to escape all these things that shall come to pass, and to stand before the Son of man.
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And in the day time he was teaching in the temple; and at night he went out, and abode in the mount that is called the mount of Olives.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And all the people came early in the morning to him in the temple, in order to hear him.
