\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And they began to enquire among themselves, which of them it was that should do this thing.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And there was also a strife among them, which of them should be accounted the greatest.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and they that exercise authority upon them are called benefactors.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]But all of you shall not be so: but he that is greatest among you, let him be as the younger; and he that is chief, as he that does serve.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]For whether is greater, he that sits at food, or he that serves? is not he that sits at food? but I am among you as he that serves.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]All of you are they which have continued with me in my temptations.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]And I appoint unto you a kingdom, as my Father has appointed unto me;
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]That all of you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And the Lord said, Simon, Simon, behold, Satan has desired to have you, that he may sift you as wheat:
