\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]And there were also two other, malefactors, led with him to be put to death.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]And when they were come to the place, which is called Calvary, there they crucified him, and the malefactors, one on the right hand, and the other on the left.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Then said Jesus, Father, forgive them; for they know not what they do. And they parted his raiment, and cast lots.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]And the people stood beholding. And the rulers also with them derided him, saying, He saved others; let him save himself, if he be Christ, the chosen of God.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]And the soldiers also mocked him, coming to him, and offering him vinegar,
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]And saying, If you be the king of the Jews, save yourself.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]And a superscription also was written over him in letters of Greek, and Latin, and Hebrew, THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And one of the malefactors which were hanged railed on him, saying, If you be Christ, save yourself and us.
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]But the other answering rebuked him, saying, Do not you fear God, seeing you are in the same condemnation?
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]And we indeed justly; for we receive the due reward of our deeds: but this man has done nothing amiss.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And he said unto Jesus, Lord, remember me when you come into your kingdom.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto you, To day shall you be with me in paradise.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And it was about the sixth hour, and there was a darkness over all the earth until the ninth hour.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into your hands I commend my spirit:  and having said thus, he gave up the spirit.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]Now when the centurion saw what was done, he glorified God, saying, Certainly this was a righteous man.
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]And all the people that came together to that sight, beholding the things which were done, stroke their breasts, and returned.
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]And all his acquaintance, and the women that followed him from Galilee, stood far off, beholding these things.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]And, behold, there was a man named Joseph, a counsellor; and he was a good man, and a just:
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX](The same had not consented to the counsel and deed of them;) he was of Arimathaea, a city of the Jews: who also himself waited for the kingdom of God.
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]This man went unto Pilate, and begged the body of Jesus.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]And he took it down, and wrapped it in linen, and laid it in a tomb that was hewn in stone, wherein never man before was laid.
\*[SUP]54\*[SUPX]And that day was the preparation, and the sabbath drew on.
\*[SUP]55\*[SUPX]And the women also, which came with him from Galilee, followed after, and beheld the tomb, and how his body was laid.
\*[SUP]56\*[SUPX]And they returned, and prepared spices and ointments; and rested the sabbath day according to the commandment.
