\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Now Jacob's well was there. Jesus therefore, being wearied with his journey, sat thus on the well: and it was about the sixth hour.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]There comes a woman of Samaria to draw water: Jesus says unto her, Give me to drink.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX](For his disciples were gone away unto the city to buy food.)
