\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]The woman says unto him, Sir, you have nothing to draw with, and the well is deep: from whence then have you that living water?
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Are you greater than our father Jacob, which gave us the well, and drank thereof himself, and his children, and his cattle?
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Jesus answered and said unto her, Whosoever drinks of this water shall thirst again:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But whosoever drinks of the water that I shall give him shall never thirst; but the water that I shall give him shall be in him a well of water springing up into everlasting life.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]The woman says unto him, Sir, give me this water, that I thirst not, neither come here to draw.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Jesus says unto her, Go, call your husband, and come here.
