fter these things Jesus walked in Galilee: for he would not walk in Jewry, because the Jews sought to kill him.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Now the Jew's feast of tabernacles was at hand.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]His brethren therefore said unto him, Depart behind, and go into Judaea, that your disciples also may see the works that you do.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]For there is no man that does any thing in secret, and he himself seeks to be known openly. If you do these things, show yourself to the world.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For neither did his brethren believe in him.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Then Jesus said unto them, My time is not yet come: but your time is always ready.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]The world cannot hate you; but me it hates, because I testify of it, that the works thereof are evil.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Go all of you up unto this feast: I go not up yet unto this feast: for my time is not yet full come.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]When he had said these words unto them, he abode still in Galilee.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]But when his brethren were gone up, then went he also up unto the feast, not openly, but as it were in secret.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Then the Jews sought him at the feast, and said, Where is he?
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And there was much murmuring among the people concerning him: for some said, He is a good man: others said, Nay; but he deceives the people.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Nevertheless no man spoke openly of him for fear of the Jews.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Now about the midst of the feast Jesus went up into the temple, and taught.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And the Jews marvelled, saying, How knows this man letters, having never learned?
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Jesus answered them, and said, My doctrine is not mine, but his that sent me.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]If any man will do his will, he shall know of the doctrine, whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]He that speaks of himself seeks his own glory: but he that seeks his glory that sent him, the same is true, and no unrighteousness is in him.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keeps the law? Why go all of you about to kill me?
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]The people answered and said, You have a devil: who goes about to kill you?
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Jesus answered and said unto them, I have done one work, and all of you all marvel.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Moses therefore gave unto you circumcision; (not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers;) and all of you on the sabbath day circumcise a man.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]If a man on the sabbath day receive circumcision, that the law of Moses should not be broken; are all of you angry at me, because I have made a man everything whole on the sabbath day?
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Then said some of them of Jerusalem, Is not this he, whom they seek to kill?
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]But, lo, he speaks boldly, and they say nothing unto him. Do the rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ?
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]Nevertheless we know this man whence he is: but when Christ comes, no man knows whence he is.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]Then cried Jesus in the temple as he taught, saying, All of you both know me, and all of you know whence I am: and I am not come of myself, but he that sent me is true, whom all of you know not.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]But I know him: for I am from him, and he has sent me.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Then they sought to take him: but no man laid hands on him, because his hour was not yet come.
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And many of the people believed on him, and said, When Christ comes, will he do more miracles than these which this man has done?
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]The Pharisees heard that the people murmured such things concerning him; and the Pharisees and the chief priests sent officers to take him.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Then said Jesus unto them, Yet a little while am I with you, and then I go unto him that sent me.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]All of you shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither all of you cannot come.
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]Then said the Jews among themselves, Where will he go, that we shall not find him? will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles, and teach the Gentiles?
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]What manner of saying  is this that he said, All of you shall seek me, and shall not find me: and where I am, thither all of you cannot come?
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]In the last day, that great day of the feast, Jesus stood and cried, saying, If any man thirst, let him come unto me, and drink.
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]He that believes on me, as the scripture has said, out of his belly shall flow rivers of living water.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX](But this spoke he of the Spirit,  which they that believe on him should receive: for the Holy Spirit  was not yet given; because that Jesus was not yet glorified.)
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]Many of the people therefore, when they heard this saying,  said, Truthfully this is the Prophet.
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Others said, This is the Christ. But some said, Shall Christ come out of Galilee?
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]Has not the scripture said, That Christ comes of the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, where David was?
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]So there was a division among the people because of him.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]And some of them would have taken him; but no man laid hands on him.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]Then came the officers to the chief priests and Pharisees; and they said unto them, Why have all of you not brought him?
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]The officers answered, Never man spoke like this man.
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]Then answered them the Pharisees, Are all of you also deceived?
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]Have any of the rulers or of the Pharisees believed on him?
\*[SUP]49\*[SUPX]But this people who knows not the law are cursed.
\*[SUP]50\*[SUPX]Nicodemus says unto them, (he that came to Jesus by night, being one of them,)
\*[SUP]51\*[SUPX]Does our law judge any man, before it hear him, and know what he does?
\*[SUP]52\*[SUPX]They answered and said unto him, Are you also of Galilee? Search, and look: for out of Galilee arises no prophet.
\*[SUP]53\*[SUPX]And every man went unto his own house.
