here was a certain man in Caesarea called Cornelius, a centurion of the band called the Italian band,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]A devout man, and one that feared God with all his house, which gave much alms to the people, and prayed to God always.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]He saw in a vision evidently about the ninth hour of the day an angel of God coming in to him, and saying unto him, Cornelius.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And when he looked on him, he was afraid, and said, What is it, Lord? And he said unto him, Your prayers and yours alms are come up for a memorial before God.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And now send men to Joppa, and call for one Simon, whose surname is Peter:
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]He lodges with one Simon a tanner, whose house is by the sea side: he shall tell you what you ought to do.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]And when the angel which spoke unto Cornelius was departed, he called two of his household servants, and a devout soldier of them that waited on him continually;
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]And when he had declared all these things unto them, he sent them to Joppa.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]On the next day, as they went on their journey, and drew nigh unto the city, Peter went up upon the housetop to pray about the sixth hour:
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And he became very hungry, and would have eaten: but while they made ready, he fell into a trance,
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And saw heaven opened, and a certain vessel descending upon him, as it had been a great sheet knit at the four corners, and let down to the earth:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Wherein were all manner of four-footed beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And there came a voice to him, Rise, Peter; kill, and eat.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But Peter said, Not so, Lord; for I have never eaten any thing that is common or unclean.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And the voice spoke unto him again the second time, What God has cleansed, that call not you common.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]This was done three times: and the vessel was received up again into heaven.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Now while Peter doubted in himself what this vision which he had seen should mean, behold, the men which were sent from Cornelius had made enquiry for Simon's house, and stood before the gate,
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And called, and asked whether Simon, which was surnamed Peter, were lodged there.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]While Peter thought on the vision, the Spirit  said unto him, Behold, three men seek you.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Arise therefore, and get you down, and go with them, doubting nothing: for I have sent them.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Then Peter went down to the men which were sent unto him from Cornelius; and said, Behold, I am he whom all of you seek: what is the cause wherefore all of you are come?
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And they said, Cornelius the centurion, a just man, and one that fears God, and of good report among all the nation of the Jews, was warned from God by an holy angel to send for you into his house, and to hear words  of you.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Then called he them in, and lodged them. And on the next day Peter went away with them, and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And the next day after they entered into Caesarea. And Cornelius waited for them, and he had called together his kinsmen and near friends.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]But Peter took him up, saying, Stand up; I myself also am a man.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And as he talked with him, he went in, and found many that were come together.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And he said unto them, All of you know how that it is an unlawful thing for a man that is a Jew to keep company, or come unto one of another nation; but God has showed me that I should not call any man common or unclean.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Therefore came I unto you without gainsaying, as soon as I was sent for: I ask therefore for what intent  all of you have sent for me?
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]And Cornelius said, Four days ago I was fasting until this hour; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]And said, Cornelius, your prayer is heard, and yours alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God.
\*[SUP]32\*[SUPX]Send therefore to Joppa, and call here Simon, whose surname is Peter; he is lodged in the house of one Simon a tanner by the sea side: who, when he comes, shall speak unto you.
\*[SUP]33\*[SUPX]Immediately therefore I sent to you; and you have well done that you are come. Now therefore are we all here present before God, to hear all things that are commanded you of God.
\*[SUP]34\*[SUPX]Then Peter opened his mouth, and said, Truthfully I perceive that God is no respecter of persons:
\*[SUP]35\*[SUPX]But in every nation he that fears him, and works righteousness, is accepted with him.
\*[SUP]36\*[SUPX]The word  which God sent unto the children of Israel, preaching peace by Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)
\*[SUP]37\*[SUPX]That word,  I say, all of you know, which was published throughout all Judaea, and began from Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;
\*[SUP]38\*[SUPX]How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit  and with power: who went about doing good, and healing all that were oppressed of the devil; for God was with him.
\*[SUP]39\*[SUPX]And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they slew and hanged on a tree:
\*[SUP]40\*[SUPX]Him God raised up the third day, and showed him openly;
\*[SUP]41\*[SUPX]Not to all the people, but unto witnesses chosen before God, even to us, who did eat and drink with him after he rose from the dead.
\*[SUP]42\*[SUPX]And he commanded us to preach unto the people, and to testify that it is he which was ordained of God to be the Judge of quick and dead.
\*[SUP]43\*[SUPX]To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name whosoever believes in him shall receive remission of sins.
\*[SUP]44\*[SUPX]While Peter yet spoke these words,  the Holy Spirit  fell on all them which heard the word.
\*[SUP]45\*[SUPX]And they of the circumcision which believed were astonished, as many as came with Peter, because that on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy Spirit.
\*[SUP]46\*[SUPX]For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered Peter,
\*[SUP]47\*[SUPX]Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, which have received the Holy Spirit  as well as we?
\*[SUP]48\*[SUPX]And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then prayed they him to tarry certain days.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 11"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "A" 2 COND 90
nd the apostles and brethren that were in Judaea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word  of God.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And when Peter was come up to Jerusalem, they that were of the circumcision contended with him,
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Saying, You went in to men uncircumcised, and did eat with them.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]But Peter rehearsed the matter from the beginning, and expounded it by order unto them, saying,
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]I was in the city of Joppa praying: and in a trance I saw a vision, A certain vessel descend, as it had been a great sheet, let down from heaven by four corners; and it came even to me:
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Upon the which when I had fastened mine eyes, I considered, and saw four-footed beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]And I heard a voice saying unto me, Arise, Peter; slay and eat.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]But I said, Not so, Lord: for nothing common or unclean has at any time entered into my mouth.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]But the voice answered me again from heaven, What God has cleansed, that call not you common.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]And this was done three times: and all were drawn up again into heaven.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And, behold, immediately there were three men already come unto the house where I was, sent from Caesarea unto me.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And the Spirit  bade me go with them, nothing doubting. Moreover these six brethren accompanied me, and we entered into the man's house:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And he showed us how he had seen an angel in his house, which stood and said unto him, Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon, whose surname is Peter;
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Who shall tell you words,  whereby you and all your house shall be saved.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And as I began to speak, the Holy Spirit  fell on them, as on us at the beginning.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Then remembered I the word  of the Lord, how that he said, John indeed baptized with water; but all of you shall be baptized with the Holy Spirit.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Forasmuch then as God gave them the like gift as he did unto us, who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ; what was I, that I could withstand God?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified God, saying, Then has God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Now they which were scattered abroad upon the persecution that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phenice, and Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the word  to none but unto the Jews only.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene, which, when they were come to Antioch, spoke unto the Grecians, preaching the LORD Jesus.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And the hand of the Lord was with them: and a great number believed, and turned unto the Lord.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Then tidings  of these things came unto the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem: and they sent forth Barnabas, that he should go as far as Antioch.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Who, when he came, and had seen the grace of God, was glad, and exhorted them all, that with purpose of heart they would cleave unto the Lord.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]For he was a good man, and full of the Holy Spirit  and of faith: and much people was added unto the Lord.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Then departed Barnabas to Tarsus, in order to seek Saul:
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And when he had found him, he brought him unto Antioch. And it came to pass, that a whole year they assembled themselves with the church, and taught much people. And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And there stood up one of them named Agabus, and signified by the Spirit  that there should be great dearth throughout all the world: which came to pass in the days of Claudius Caesar.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]Then the disciples, every man according to his ability, determined to send relief unto the brethren which dwelt in Judaea:
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]Which also they did, and sent it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.
