\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]There is none that understands, there is none that seeks after God.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]They are all gone out of the way, they are together become useless; there is none that does good, no, not one.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Their throat is an open tomb; with their tongues they have used deceit; the poison of asps is under their lips:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Their feet are swift to shed blood:
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Destruction and misery are in their ways:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And the way of peace have they not known:
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]There is no fear of God before their eyes.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Now we know that what things whatsoever the law says, it says to them who are under the law: that every mouth may be stopped, and all the world may become guilty before God.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Therefore by the deeds of the law there shall no flesh be justified in his sight: for by the law is the knowledge of sin.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]But now the righteousness of God without the law is manifested, being witnessed by the law and the prophets;
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Even the righteousness of God which is by faith of Jesus Christ unto all and upon all them that believe: for there is no difference:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]For all have sinned, and come short of the glory of God;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Being justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus:
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Whom God has set forth to be a propitiation through faith in his blood, to declare his righteousness for the remission of sins that are past, through the forbearance of God;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]To declare, I say, at this time his righteousness: that he might be just, and the justifier of him which believes in Jesus.
