aul called to be an apostle of Jesus Christ through the will of God, and Sosthenes our brother,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Unto the church of God which is at Corinth, to them that are sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, with all that in every place call upon the name of Jesus Christ our Lord, both their's and our's:
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Grace be unto you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]I thank my God always on your behalf, for the grace of God which is given you by Jesus Christ;
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]That in every thing all of you are enriched by him, in all utterance,  and in all knowledge;
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Even as the testimony of Christ was confirmed in you:
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]So that all of you come behind in no gift; waiting for the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ:
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Who shall also confirm you unto the end, that all of you may be blameless in the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]God is faithful, by whom all of you were called unto the fellowship of his Son Jesus Christ our Lord.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Now I plead to you, brethren, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that all of you all speak the same thing, and that there be no divisions among you; but that all of you be perfectly joined together in the same mind and in the same judgment.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For it has been declared unto me of you, my brethren, by them which are of the house of Chloe, that there are contentions among you.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Now this I say, that every one of you says, I am of Paul; and I of Apollos; and I of Cephas; and I of Christ.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Is Christ divided? was Paul crucified for you? or were all of you baptized in the name of Paul?
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]I thank God that I baptized none of you, but Crispus and Gaius;
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Lest any should say that I had baptized in mine own name.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And I baptized also the household of Stephanas: besides, I know not whether I baptized any other.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]For Christ sent me not to baptize, but to preach the gospel: not with wisdom of words,  lest the cross of Christ should be made of no effect.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]For the preaching  of the cross is to them that perish foolishness; but unto us which are saved it is the power of God.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]For it is written, I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, and will bring to nothing the understanding of the prudent.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Where is the wise? where is the scribe? where is the disputer of this world? has not God made foolish the wisdom of this world?
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]For after that in the wisdom of God the world by wisdom knew not God, it pleased God by the foolishness of preaching to save them that believe.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]For the Jews require a sign, and the Greeks seek after wisdom:
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But we preach Christ crucified, unto the Jews a stumbling block, and unto the Greeks foolishness;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]But unto them which are called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God, and the wisdom of God.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]Because the foolishness of God is wiser than men; and the weakness of God is stronger than men.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]For all of you see your calling, brethren, how that not many wise men after the flesh, not many mighty, not many noble, are called:
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]But God has chosen the foolish things of the world to confound the wise; and God has chosen the weak things of the world to confound the things which are mighty;
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And base things of the world, and things which are despised, has God chosen, yea, and things which are not, to bring to nothing things that are:
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]That no flesh should glory in his presence.
\*[SUP]30\*[SUPX]But of him are all of you in Christ Jesus, who of God is made unto us wisdom, and righteousness, and sanctification, and redemption:
\*[SUP]31\*[SUPX]That, according as it is written, He that glories, let him glory in the Lord.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 2"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "A" 2 COND 90
nd I, brethren, when I came to you, came not with excellency of speech  or of wisdom, declaring unto you the testimony of God.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For I determined not to know any thing among you, save Jesus Christ, and him crucified.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And I was with you in weakness, and in fear, and in much trembling.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And my speech  and my preaching was not with enticing words  of man's wisdom, but in demonstration of the Spirit  and of power:
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]That your faith should not stand in the wisdom of men, but in the power of God.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Nevertheless we speak wisdom among them that are perfect: yet not the wisdom of this world, nor of the princes of this world, that come to nothing:
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]But we speak the wisdom of God in a mystery, even the hidden wisdom, which God ordained before the world unto our glory:
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Which none of the princes of this world knew: for had they known it, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]But as it is written, Eye has not seen, nor ear heard, neither have entered into the heart of man, the things which God has prepared for them that love him.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]But God has revealed them unto us by his Spirit:  for the Spirit  searches all things, yea, the deep things of God.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For what man knows the things of a man, save the spirit  of man which is in him? even so the things of God knows no man, but the Spirit  of God.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Now we have received, not the spirit  of the world, but the spirit  which is of God; that we might know the things that are freely given to us of God.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Which things also we speak, not in the words  which man's wisdom teaches, but which the Holy Spirit  teaches; comparing spiritual things with spiritual.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But the natural man receives not the things of the Spirit  of God: for they are foolishness unto him: neither can he know them, because they are spiritually discerned.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]But he that is spiritual judges all things, yet he himself is judged of no man.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For who has known the mind of the Lord, that he may instruct him? But we have the mind of Christ.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 3"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "A" 2 COND 90
nd I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, even as unto babes in Christ.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]I have fed you with milk, and not with food: for until now all of you were not able to bear it, neither yet now are all of you able.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For all of you are yet carnal: for whereas there is among you envying, and strife, and divisions, are all of you not carnal, and walk as men?
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]For while one says, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are all of you not carnal?
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom all of you believed, even as the Lord gave to every man?
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]I have planted, Apollos watered; but God gave the increase.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]So then neither is he that plants any thing, neither he that waters; but God that gives the increase.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Now he that plants and he that waters are one: and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labour.
