ow concerning the collection for the saints, as I have given order to the churches of Galatia, even so do all of you.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Upon the first day of the week let every one of you lay by him in store, as God has prospered him, that there be no gatherings when I come.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And when I come, whomsoever all of you shall approve by your letters, them will I send to bring your liberality unto Jerusalem.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And if it be meet that I go also, they shall go with me.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Now I will come unto you, when I shall pass through Macedonia: for I do pass through Macedonia.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]And it may be that I will abide, yea, and winter with you, that all of you may bring me on my journey anywhere I go.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For I will not see you now by the way; but I trust to tarry a while with you, if the Lord permit.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]But I will tarry at Ephesus until Pentecost.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]For a great door and effectual is opened unto me, and there are many adversaries.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Now if Timotheus come, see that he may be with you without fear: for he works the work of the Lord, as I also do.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Let no man therefore despise him: but conduct him forth in peace, that he may come unto me: for I look for him with the brethren.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]As concerning our brother Apollos, I greatly desired him to come unto you with the brethren: but his will was not at all to come at this time; but he will come when he shall have convenient time.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Watch all of you, stand fast in the faith, quit you like men, be strong.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Let all your things be done with love.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]I plead to (all of you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first-fruits of Achaia, and that they have addicted themselves to the ministry of the saints,)
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]That all of you submit yourselves unto such, and to every one that helps with us, and labours.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]I am glad of the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus: for that which was lacking on your part they have supplied.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]For they have refreshed my spirit  and your's: therefore acknowledge all of you them that are such.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]The churches of Asia salute you. Aquila and Priscilla salute you much in the Lord, with the church that is in their house.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]All the brethren greet you. Greet all of you one another with an holy kiss.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]The salutation of me Paul with mine own hand.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]If any man love not the Lord Jesus Christ, let him be Anathema Maranatha.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]My love  be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.
