\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Now he that has wrought us for the very same thing is God, who also has given unto us the earn of the Spirit.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Therefore we are always confident, knowing that, whilst we are at home in the body, we are absent from the Lord:
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX](For we walk by faith, not by sight:)
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]We are confident, I say, and willing rather to be absent from the body, and to be present with the Lord.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Wherefore we labour, that, whether present or absent, we may be accepted of him.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For we must all appear before the judgment seat of Christ; that every one may receive the things done in his body, according to that he has done, whether it be good or bad.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Knowing therefore the terror of the Lord, we persuade men; but we are made manifest unto God; and I trust also are made manifest in your consciences.
