\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]For in Jesus Christ neither circumcision avails any thing, nor uncircumcision; but faith which works by love.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]All of you did run well; who did hinder you that all of you should not obey the truth?
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]This persuasion comes not of him that calls you.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]A little leaven leavens the whole lump.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]I have confidence in you through the Lord, that all of you will be none otherwise minded: but he that troubles you shall bear his judgment, whosoever he be.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]And I, brethren, if I yet preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? then is the offence of the cross ceased.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]I would they were even cut off which trouble you.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]For, brethren, all of you have been called unto liberty; only use not liberty for an occasion to the flesh, but by love  serve one another.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]For all the law is fulfilled in one word,  even in this; You shall love your neighbour as yourself.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]But if all of you bite and devour one another, take heed that all of you be not consumed one of another.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]This I say then, Walk in the Spirit,  and all of you shall not fulfill the lust of the flesh.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]For the flesh lusts against the Spirit,  and the Spirit  against the flesh: and these are contrary the one to the other: so that all of you cannot do the things that all of you would.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]But if all of you be led of the Spirit,  all of you are not under the law.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Now the works of the flesh are manifest, which are these; Adultery, fornication, uncleanness, lasciviousness,
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Idolatry, witchcraft, hatred, variance, worldy jealousies, wrath, strife, seditions, heresies,
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Envyings, murders, drunkenness, revellings, and such like: of the which I tell you before, as I have also told you in time past, that they which do such things shall not inherit the kingdom of God.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]But the fruit of the Spirit  is love,  joy, peace, longsuffering, gentleness, goodness, faith,
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Meekness, wilful restrain: against such there is no law.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And they that are Christ's have crucified the flesh with the affections and lusts.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]If we live in the Spirit,  let us also walk in the Spirit.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]Let us not be desirous of vain glory, provoking one another, envying one another.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 6"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "B" 2 COND 90
rethren, if a man be overtaken in a fault, all of you which are spiritual, restore such an one in the spirit  of meekness; considering yourself, lest you also be tempted.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Bear all of you one another's burdens, and so fulfill the law of Christ.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For if a man think himself to be something, when he is nothing, he deceives himself.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]But let every man prove his own work, and then shall he have rejoicing in himself alone, and not in another.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For every man shall bear his own burden.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Let him that is taught in the word  communicate unto him that teaches in all good things.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Be not deceived; God is not mocked: for whatsoever a man sows, that shall he also reap.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]For he that sows to his flesh shall of the flesh reap corruption; but he that sows to the Spirit  shall of the Spirit  reap life everlasting.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And let us not be weary in well doing: for in due season we shall reap, if we faint not.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]As we have therefore opportunity, let us do good unto all men, especially unto them who are of the household of faith.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]All of you see how large a letter I have written unto you with mine own hand.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]As many as desire to make a fair show in the flesh, they constrain you to be circumcised; only lest they should suffer persecution for the cross of Christ.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]For neither they themselves who are circumcised keep the law; but desire to have you circumcised, that they may glory in your flesh.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But God forbid that I should glory, save in the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom the world is crucified unto me, and I unto the world.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision avails any thing, nor uncircumcision, but a new creature.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And as many as walk according to this rule, peace be on them, and mercy, and upon the Israel of God.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]From henceforth let no man trouble me: for I bear in my body the marks of the Lord Jesus.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Brethren, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.  Amen.
