nd you has he quickened, who were dead in trespasses and sins;
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Wherein in time past all of you walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit  that now works in the children of disobedience:
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Among whom also we all had our conversation in times past in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the mind; and were by nature the children of wrath, even as others.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]But God, who is rich in mercy, for his great love  wherewith he loved us,
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Even when we were dead in sins, has quickened us together with Christ, (by grace all of you are saved;)
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]And has raised us up together, and made us sit together in heavenly places in Christ Jesus:
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]That in the ages to come he might show the exceeding riches of his grace in his kindness toward us through Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]For by grace are all of you saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Not of works, lest any man should boast.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For we are his workmanship, created in Christ Jesus unto good works, which God has before ordained that we should walk in them.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Wherefore remember, that all of you being in time past Gentiles in the flesh, who are called Uncircumcision by that which is called the Circumcision in the flesh made by hands;
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]That at that time all of you were without Christ, being aliens from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of promise, having no hope, and without God in the world:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]But now in Christ Jesus all of you who sometimes were far off are made nigh by the blood of Christ.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]For he is our peace, who has made both one, and has broken down the middle wall of partition between us;
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Having abolished in his flesh the enmity, even the law of commandments contained in ordinances; in order to make in himself of two one new man, so making peace;
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And that he might reconcile both unto God in one body by the cross, having slain the enmity thereby:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And came and preached peace to you which were far off, and to them that were nigh.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]For through him we both have access by one Spirit  unto the Father.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Now therefore all of you are no more strangers and foreigners, but fellow citizens with the saints, and of the household of God;
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]And are built upon the foundation of the apostles and prophets, Jesus Christ himself being the chief corner stone;
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]In whom all the building fitly framed together grows unto an holy temple in the Lord:
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]In whom all of you also are built together for an habitation of God through the Spirit.
