\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Finally, brethren, whatsoever things are true, whatsoever things are honest, whatsoever things are just, whatsoever things are pure, whatsoever things are lovely, whatsoever things are of good report; if there be any virtue, and if there be any praise, think on these things.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Those things, which all of you have both learned, and received, and heard, and seen in me, do: and the God of peace shall be with you.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]But I rejoiced in the Lord greatly, that now at the last your care of me has flourished again; wherein all of you were also careful, but all of you lacked opportunity.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Not that I speak in respect of lack: for I have learned, in whatsoever state I am, therewith to be content.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]I know both how to be brought low, and I know how to abound: every where and in all things I am instructed both to be full and to be hungry, both to abound and to suffer need.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]I can do all things through Christ which strengthens me.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Notwithstanding all of you have well done, that all of you did communicate with my affliction.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Now all of you Philippians know also, that in the beginning of the gospel, when I departed from Macedonia, no church communicated with me as concerning  giving and receiving, but all of you only.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For even in Thessalonica all of you sent once and again unto my necessity.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Not because I desire a gift: but I desire fruit that may abound to your account.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]But I have all, and abound: I am full, having received of Epaphroditus the things which were sent from you, an odour of a sweet smell, a sacrifice acceptable, well-pleasing to God.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]But my God shall supply all your need according to his riches in glory by Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Now unto God and our Father be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Salute every saint in Christ Jesus. The brethren which are with me greet you.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]All the saints salute you, chiefly they that are of Caesar's household.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
