.\"
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 1"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "P" 2 COND 90
aul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, according to the promise of life which is in Christ Jesus,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]To Timothy, my dearly beloved son: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]I thank God, whom I serve from my forefathers with pure conscience, that without ceasing I have remembrance of you in my prayers night and day;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Greatly desiring to see you, being mindful of your tears, that I may be filled with joy;
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]When I call to remembrance the sincere faith that is in you, which dwelt first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice; and I am persuaded that in you also.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Wherefore I put you in remembrance that you stir up the gift of God, which is in you by the putting on of my hands.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For God has not given us the spirit  of fear; but of power, and of love,  and of a sound mind.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Be not you therefore ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner: but be you partaker of the afflictions of the gospel according to the power of God;
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Who has saved us, and called us with an holy calling, not according to our works, but according to his own purpose and grace, which was given us in Christ Jesus before the world began,
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]But is now made manifest by the appearing of our Saviour Jesus Christ, who has abolished death, and has brought life and immortality to light through the gospel:
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Unto which I am appointed a preacher, and an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]For the which cause I also suffer these things: nevertheless I am not ashamed: for I know whom I have believed, and am persuaded that he is able to keep that which I have committed unto him against that day.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Hold fast the form of sound words,  which you have heard of me, in faith and love  which is in Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]That good thing which was committed unto you keep by the Holy Spirit  which dwells in us.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]This you know, that all they which are in Asia be turned away from me; of whom are Phygellus and Hermogenes.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]The Lord give mercy unto the house of Onesiphorus; for he often refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chain:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]But, when he was in Rome, he sought me out very diligently, and found me.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]The Lord grant unto him that he may find mercy of the Lord in that day: and in how many things he ministered unto me at Ephesus, you know very well.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 2"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "Y" 2 COND 90
ou therefore, my son, be strong in the grace that is in Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And the things that you have heard of me among many witnesses, the same commit you to faithful men, who shall be able to teach others also.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]You therefore endure hardness, as a good soldier of Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]No man that wars entangles himself with the affairs of this life; that he may please him who has chosen him to be a soldier.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And if a man also strive for masteries, yet is he not crowned, except he strive lawfully.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]The farmer that labours must be first partaker of the fruits.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Consider what I say; and the Lord give you understanding in all things.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Remember that Jesus Christ of the seed of David was raised from the dead according to my gospel:
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Wherein I suffer trouble, as an evil doer, even unto bonds; but the word  of God is not bound.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Therefore I endure all things for the elect's sakes, that they may also obtain the salvation which is in Christ Jesus with eternal glory.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]It is a faithful saying:  For if we be dead with him, we shall also live with him:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]If we suffer, we shall also reign with him: if we deny him, he also will deny us:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]If we believe not, yet he abides faithful: he cannot deny himself.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Of these things put them in remembrance, charging them before the Lord that they strive not about words to no profit, but to the subverting of the hearers.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Study to show yourself approved unto God, a workman that needs not to be ashamed, rightly dividing the word  of truth.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]But shun profane and vain babblings: for they will increase unto more ungodliness.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And their word  will eat as does a canker: of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus;
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Who concerning the truth have erred, saying that the resurrection is past already; and overthrow the faith of some.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Nevertheless the foundation of God stands sure, having this seal, The Lord knows them that are his. And, Let every one that names the name of Christ depart from iniquity.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]But in a great house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of earth; and some to honour, and some to dishonour.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]If a man therefore purge himself from these, he shall be a vessel unto honour, sanctified, and meet for the master's use, and prepared unto every good work.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Flee also youthful lusts: but follow righteousness, faith, love,  peace, with them that call on the Lord out of a pure heart.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]But foolish and unlearned questions avoid, knowing that they do gender strifes.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And the servant of the Lord must not strive; but be gentle unto all men, able to teach, patient,
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]In meekness instructing those that oppose themselves; if God possibly will give them repentance to the acknowledging of the truth;
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]And that they may recover themselves out of the snare of the devil, who are taken captive by him at his will.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 3"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "T" 2 COND 90
his know also, that in the last days dangerous times shall come.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]For men shall be lovers of their own selves, covetous, boasters, proud, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful, unholy,
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Without natural affection, trucebreakers, false accusers, incontinent, fierce, despisers of those that are good,
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Traitors, rebellious, high-minded, lovers of pleasures more than lovers of God;
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Having a form of godliness, but denying the power thereof: from such turn away.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]For of this sort are they which creep into houses, and lead captive silly women laden with sins, led away with divers lusts,
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Ever learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Now as Jannes and Jambres withstood Moses, so do these also resist the truth: men of corrupt minds, reprobate concerning the faith.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]But they shall proceed no further: for their folly shall be manifest unto all men, as their's also was.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]But you have fully known my doctrine, manner of life, purpose, faith, longsuffering, love,  patience,
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Persecutions, afflictions, which came unto me at Antioch, at Iconium, at Lystra; what persecutions I endured: but out of them all the Lord delivered me.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Yea, and all that will live godly in Christ Jesus shall suffer persecution.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]But evil men and seducers shall wax worse and worse, deceiving, and being deceived.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But continue you in the things which you have learned and have been assured of, knowing of whom you have learned them;
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]And that from a child you have known the holy scriptures, which are able to make you wise unto salvation through faith which is in Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]All scripture is given by inspiration of God, and is profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for instruction in righteousness:
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]That the man of God may be perfect, thoroughly furnished unto all good works.
