.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "I" 2 COND 90
 charge you therefore before God, and the Lord Jesus Christ, who shall judge the quick and the dead at his appearing and his kingdom;
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Preach the word;  be instant in season, out of season; reprove, rebuke, exhort with all longsuffering and doctrine.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]For the time will come when they will not endure sound doctrine; but after their own lusts shall they heap to themselves teachers, having itching ears;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And they shall turn away their ears from the truth, and shall be turned unto fables.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]But watch you in all things, endure afflictions, do the work of an evangelist, make full proof of your ministry.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]For I am now ready to be offered, and the time of my departure is at hand.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]I have fought a good fight, I have finished my course, I have kept the faith:
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Henceforth there is laid up for me a crown of righteousness, which the Lord, the righteous judge, shall give me at that day: and not to me only, but unto all them also that love his appearing.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Do your diligence to come shortly unto me:
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For Demas has forsaken me, having loved this present world, and is departed unto Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, Titus unto Dalmatia.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Only Luke is with me. Take Mark, and bring him with you: for he is profitable to me for the ministry.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]And Tychicus have I sent to Ephesus.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]The coat that I left at Troas with Carpus, when you come, bring with you, and the books, but especially the parchments.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]Alexander the coppersmith did me much evil: the Lord reward him according to his works:
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Of whom be you ware also; for he has greatly withstood our words.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]At my first answer no man stood with me, but all men forsook me: I pray God that it may not be laid to their charge.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Notwithstanding the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me; that by me the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]And the Lord shall deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me unto his heavenly kingdom: to whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]Salute Prisca and Aquila, and the household of Onesiphorus.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Erastus abode at Corinth: but Trophimus have I left at Miletum sick.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Do your diligence to come before winter. Eubulus greets you, and Pudens, and Linus, and Claudia, and all the brethren.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]The Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.  Grace be with you. Amen.
