aul, a prisoner of Jesus Christ, and Timothy our brother, unto Philemon our dearly beloved, and fellow labourer,
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And to our beloved Apphia, and Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the church in your house:
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]I thank my God, making mention of you always in my prayers,
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]Hearing of your love  and faith, which you have toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all saints;
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]That the communication of your faith may become effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]For we have great joy and consolation in your love,  because the bowels of the saints are refreshed by you, brother.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Wherefore, though I might be much bold in Christ to admonish you that which is convenient,
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Yet for love's  sake I rather plead to you, being such an one as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]I plead to you for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten in my bonds:
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Which in time past was to you useless, but now profitable to you and to me:
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Whom I have sent again: you therefore receive him, that is, mine own bowels:
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Whom I would have retained with me, that in your position he might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But without your mind would I do nothing; that your benefit should not be as it were of necessity, but willingly.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]For perhaps he therefore departed for a season, that you should receive him for ever;
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Not now as a servant, but above a servant, a brother beloved, specially to me, but how much more unto you, both in the flesh, and in the Lord?
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]If you count me therefore a partner, receive him as myself.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]If he has wronged you, or owes you ought, put that on mine account;
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]I Paul have written it with mine own hand, I will repay it: although it be I do not say to you how you owe unto me even yours own self besides.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Yea, brother, let me have joy of you in the Lord: refresh my bowels in the Lord.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Having confidence in your obedience I wrote unto you, knowing that you will also do more than I say.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]But likewise prepare me also a lodging: for I trust that through your prayers I shall be given unto you.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]There salute you Epaphras, my fellow-prisoner in Christ Jesus;
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellow labourers.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.  Amen.
