\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]How shall we escape, if we neglect so great salvation; which at the first began to be spoken by the Lord, and was confirmed unto us by them that heard him;
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]God also bearing them witness, both with signs and wonders, and with divers miracles, and gifts of the Holy Spirit,  according to his own will?
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]For unto the angels has he not put in subjection the world to come, whereof we speak.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]But one in a certain place testified, saying, What is man, that you are mindful of him? or the son of man that you visit him?
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]You made him a little lower than the angels; you crowned him with glory and honour, and did set him over the works of your hands:
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]You have put all things in subjection under his feet. For in that he put all in subjection under him, he left nothing that is not put under him. But now we see not yet all things put under him.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]But we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels for the suffering of death, crowned with glory and honour; that he by the grace of God should taste death for every man.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For it became him, for whom are all things, and by whom are all things, in bringing many sons unto glory, to make the captain of their salvation perfect through sufferings.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For both he that santifies and they who are sanctified are all of one: for which cause he is not ashamed to call them brethren,
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Saying, I will declare your name unto my brethren, in the midst of the church will I sing praise unto you.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And again, I will put my trust in him. And again, Behold I and the children which God has given me.
