.PP
.DROPCAP "F" 2 COND 90
or every high priest taken from among men is ordained for men in things pertaining to God, that he may offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins:
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Who can have compassion on the ignorant, and on them that are out of the way; for that he himself also is compassed with infirmity.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And by reason hereof he ought, as for the people, so also for himself, to offer for sins.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]And no man takes this honour unto himself, but he that is called of God, as was Aaron.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]So also Christ glorified not himself to be made an high priest; but he that said unto him, You are my Son, to day have I begotten you.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]As he says also in another place, You are a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Who in the days of his flesh, when he had offered up prayers and supplications with strong crying and tears unto him that was able to save him from death, and was heard in that he feared;
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Though he were a Son, yet learned he obedience by the things which he suffered;
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]And being made perfect, he became the author of eternal salvation unto all them that obey him;
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Called of God an high priest after the order of Melchisedec.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Of whom we have  many things to say,  and hard to be uttered, seeing all of you are dull of hearing.
