\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Not rendering evil for evil, or railing for railing: but contrariwise blessing; knowing that all of you are thereunto called, that all of you should inherit a blessing.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]For he that will love life, and see good days, let him refrain his tongue from evil, and his lips that they speak no guile:
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Let him shun evil, and do good; let him seek peace, and pursue it.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and his ears are open unto their prayers: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]And who is he that will harm you, if all of you be followers of that which is good?
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]But and if all of you suffer for righteousness' sake, happy are all of you: and be not afraid of their terror, neither be troubled;
