\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]For it is better, if the will of God be so, that all of you suffer for well doing, than for evil doing.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]For Christ also has once suffered for sins, the just for the unjust, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh, but quickened by the Spirit:
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]By which also he went and preached unto the spirits  in prison;
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]Which sometime were disobedient, when once the longsuffering of God waited in the days of Noah, while the ark was a preparing, wherein few, that is, eight souls were saved by water.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]The like figure unto which even baptism does also now save us (not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good conscience toward God,) by the resurrection of Jesus Christ:
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Who is gone into heaven, and is on the right hand of God; angels and authorities and powers being made subject unto him.
