y little children, these things write I unto you, that all of you sin not. And if any man sin, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous:
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]And he is the propitiation for our sins: and not for our's only, but also for the sins of the whole world.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And hereby we do know that we know him, if we keep his commandments.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]He that says, I know him, and keeps not his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]But whoso keeps his word,  in him verily is the love  of God perfected: hereby know we that we are in him.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]He that says he abides in him ought himself also so to walk, even as he walked.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Brethren, I write no new commandment unto you, but an old commandment which all of you had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word  which all of you have heard from the beginning.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]Again, a new commandment I write unto you, which thing is true in him and in you: because the darkness is past, and the true light now shines.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]He that says he is in the light, and hates his brother, is in darkness even until now.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]He that loves his brother abides in the light, and there is none occasion of stumbling in him.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]But he that hates his brother is in darkness, and walks in darkness, and knows not where he goes, because that darkness has blinded his eyes.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]I write unto you, little children, because your sins are forgiven you for his name's sake.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]I write unto you, fathers, because all of you have known him that is from the beginning. I write unto you, young men, because all of you have overcome the wicked one. I write unto you, little children, because all of you have known the Father.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]I have written unto you, fathers, because all of you have known him that is from the beginning. I have written unto you, young men, because all of you are strong, and the word  of God abides in you, and all of you have overcome the wicked one.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Love not the world, neither the things that are in the world. If any man love the world, the love  of the Father is not in him.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]For all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, is not of the Father, but is of the world.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]And the world passes away, and the lust thereof: but he that does the will of God abides for ever.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]Little children, it is the last time: and as all of you have heard that antichrist shall come, even now are there many antichrists; whereby we know that it is the last time.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would no doubt have continued with us: but they went out, that they might be made manifest that they were not all of us.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]But all of you have an anointing from the Holy One, and all of you know all things.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]I have not written unto you because all of you know not the truth, but because all of you know it, and that no lie is of the truth.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]Who is a liar but he that denies that Jesus is the Christ? He is antichrist, that denies the Father and the Son.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]Whosoever denies the Son, the same has not the Father: he that acknowledges the Son has the Father also.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]Let that therefore abide in you, which all of you have heard from the beginning. If that which all of you have heard from the beginning shall remain in you, all of you also shall continue in the Son, and in the Father.
\*[SUP]25\*[SUPX]And this is the promise that he has promised us, even eternal life.
\*[SUP]26\*[SUPX]These things have I written unto you concerning them that seduce you.
\*[SUP]27\*[SUPX]But the anointing which all of you have received of him abides in you, and all of you need not that any man teach you: but as the same anointing teaches you of all things, and is truth, and is no lie, and even as it has taught you, all of you shall abide in him.
\*[SUP]28\*[SUPX]And now, little children, abide in him; that, when he shall appear, we may have confidence, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.
\*[SUP]29\*[SUPX]If all of you know that he is righteous, all of you know that every one that does righteousness is born of him.
.HEADING 2 "Chapter 3"
.\"
.PP
.DROPCAP "B" 2 COND 90
ehold, what manner of love  the Father has bestowed upon us, that we should be called the sons of God: therefore the world knows us not, because it knew him not.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Beloved, now are we the sons of God, and it does not yet appear what we shall be: but we know that, when he shall appear, we shall be like him; for we shall see him as he is.
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And every man that has this hope in him purifies himself, even as he is pure.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]Whosoever commits sin trangresses also the law: for sin is the transgression of the law.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]And all of you know that he was manifested to take away our sins; and in him is no sin.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]Whosoever abides in him sins not: whosoever sins has not seen him, neither known him.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Little children, let no man deceive you: he that does righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]He that commits sin is of the devil; for the devil sins from the beginning. For this purpose the Son of God was manifested, that he might destroy the works of the devil.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]Whosoever is born of God does not commit sin; for his seed remains in him: and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]In this the children of God are manifest, and the children of the devil: whosoever does not righteousness is not of God, neither he that loves not his brother.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]For this is the message that all of you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]Not as Cain, who was of that wicked one, and slew his brother. And wherefore slew he him? Because his own works were evil, and his brother's righteous.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Marvel not, my brethren, if the world hate you.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]We know that we have passed from death unto life, because we love the brethren. He that loves not his brother abides in death.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Whosoever hates his brother is a murderer: and all of you know that no murderer has eternal life abiding in him.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]Hereby perceive we the love  of God, because he laid down his life for us: and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]But whoso has this world's good, and sees his brother have need, and shuts up his bowels of compassion from him, how dwells the love  of God in him?
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]My little children, let us not love in word,  neither in tongue; but in deed and in truth.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]And hereby we know that we are of the truth, and shall assure our hearts before him.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]For if our heart condemn us, God is greater than our heart, and knows all things.
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]Beloved, if our heart condemn us not, then have we confidence toward God.
\*[SUP]22\*[SUPX]And whatsoever we ask, we receive of him, because we keep his commandments, and do those things that are pleasing in his sight.
\*[SUP]23\*[SUPX]And this is his commandment, That we should believe on the name of his Son Jesus Christ, and love one another, as he gave us commandment.
\*[SUP]24\*[SUPX]And he that keeps his commandments dwells in him, and he in him. And hereby we know that he abides in us, by the Spirit  which he has given us.
