eloved, believe not every spirit,  but try the spirits  whether they are of God: because many false prophets are gone out into the world.
\*[SUP]2\*[SUPX]Hereby know all of you the Spirit  of God: Every spirit  that confesses that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is of God:
\*[SUP]3\*[SUPX]And every spirit  that confesses not that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit of antichrist, whereof all of you have heard that it should come; and even now already is it in the world.
\*[SUP]4\*[SUPX]All of you are of God, little children, and have overcome them: because greater is he that is in you, than he that is in the world.
\*[SUP]5\*[SUPX]They are of the world: therefore speak they of the world, and the world hears them.
\*[SUP]6\*[SUPX]We are of God: he that knows God hears us; he that is not of God hears not us. Hereby know we the spirit  of truth, and the spirit  of error.
\*[SUP]7\*[SUPX]Beloved, let us love one another: for love  is of God; and every one that loves is born of God, and knows God.
\*[SUP]8\*[SUPX]He that loves not knows not God; for God is love.
\*[SUP]9\*[SUPX]In this was manifested the love  of God toward us, because that God sent his only begotten Son into the world, that we might live through him.
\*[SUP]10\*[SUPX]Herein is love,  not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins.
\*[SUP]11\*[SUPX]Beloved, if God so loved us, we ought also to love one another.
\*[SUP]12\*[SUPX]No man has seen God at any time. If we love one another, God dwells in us, and his love  is perfected in us.
\*[SUP]13\*[SUPX]Hereby know we that we dwell in him, and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.
\*[SUP]14\*[SUPX]And we have seen and do testify that the Father sent the Son to be the Saviour of the world.
\*[SUP]15\*[SUPX]Whosoever shall confess that Jesus is the Son of God, God dwells in him, and he in God.
\*[SUP]16\*[SUPX]And we have known and believed the love  that God has to us. God is love;  and he that dwells in love  dwells in God, and God in him.
\*[SUP]17\*[SUPX]Herein is our love  made perfect, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment: because as he is, so are we in this world.
\*[SUP]18\*[SUPX]There is no fear in love;  but perfect love  casts out fear: because fear has torment. He that fears is not made perfect in love.
\*[SUP]19\*[SUPX]We love him, because he first loved us.
\*[SUP]20\*[SUPX]If a man say, I love God, and hates his brother, he is a liar: for he that loves not his brother whom he has seen, how can he love God whom he has not seen?
\*[SUP]21\*[SUPX]And this commandment have we from him, That he who loves God love his brother also.
